<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4617] Error when running groovysh with verbose option (-v)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4617</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When starting groovysh with the verbose option (-v) &quot;groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException&quot; is thrown.&lt;br/&gt;
See bellow:&lt;br/&gt;
**********&lt;br/&gt;
C:\&amp;gt;groovysh -v&lt;br/&gt;
Groovy Shell (1.7.6, JVM: 1.6.0_07)&lt;br/&gt;
Type &apos;help&apos; or &apos;\h&apos; for help.&lt;br/&gt;
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
groovy:000&amp;gt; a = &quot;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException:&lt;br/&gt;
No such property: buffer for class: org.codehaus.groovy.tools.shell.Groovysh&lt;br/&gt;
Possible solutions: buffers, runner&lt;br/&gt;
        at java_lang_Runnable$run.call (Unknown Source)&lt;br/&gt;
groovy:000&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
**********&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
                <environment>Windows 5.1.2600 Service Pack 3 Build 2600&lt;br/&gt;
java version &amp;quot;1.6.0_07&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Groovy Shell 1.7.6</environment>
